UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Charles G. JOHNSON, Appellee. No. 7482. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May 21, 1934. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and M. G. Gallaher, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los An-geles, Cal. (E. D. Fooks, of Los Angeles, Cal., of counsel), for the United States. David Spaulding, of West Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
